b'' b'fred gilham asks whether it is true that goedel wrote a version of' b'the ontological argument for the existence of god.' b'' b'yes, it is true. someone has published a rebuttal pointing out' b'certain flaws in the argument, and recently professor c anthony' b'anderson, of the philosophy department of the university of' b'minnesota, has written a revised version of the argument, perhaps' b'free of flaws, and at any rate free of the flaws complained of in' b'the original version. he has sent me a copy, which i still have (i' b'saw it last week when i was looking for something else), and when it' b'surfaces again i can supply particulars. my guess is that it is' b'being published (or already has been) in the journal of symbolic' b'logic.' b'' b'yours,' b'james kiefer' 